    oakcurric:thread-modern-literature-strand-1-identity-belonging-and-community .

oakcurric:unit-170
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Poetry anthology: continued study"@en ;
  curric:slug "poetry-anthology-continued-study" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupis read and analyse three more poems from the 'Power and
  Conflict' anthology. Pupils complete two lessons about each poem: one on understanding and
  one on analysis. At the end of the unit, pupils analyse themes from across the anthology
  and write a sophisticated comparative essay,"""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils build on their understanding of the 'Power and
  Conflict' anthology from its 'first study' unit. They now read the more complex poems from
  the anthology, and start to make more nuanced and tentative comparisons across poems in the
  anthology. They also start to write more sophisticated comparative responses, which draw on
  their poetry knowledge and analytical comparative skills from across the 'appreciation of
  poetry' thread. By the end of this unit, pupils can craft nuanced and extended comparative
  poetry essays about the themes in the 'Power and Conflict' anthology.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-170-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-170-2 ,
