oakcurric:unit-3708
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Modern text: third deep dive"@en ;
  curric:slug "modern-text-third-deep-dive" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore how Pinnock's use of stragecraft in 'Leave Taking'
  contributes to the play's themes and ideas. They first look at an overview of the play's
  stagecraft before exploring different settings and techniques in detail. They finally
  write an essay on generational conflict."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' understanding of 'Leave Taking' from
  the second deep dive, 'An intersectional analysis'. In that unit, pupils developed deep and
  nuanced interpretations of the play's complex ideas. In this unit, pupils develop that
  thinking by seeing how Pinnock uses stagecraft to develop and support those ideas.""" ;
  curric:id "3708"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.465219Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-modern-literature-strand-1-identity-belonging-and-community .

oakcurric:unit-168
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Shakespeare: first deep dive"@en ;
  curric:slug "macbeth-a-tragic-hero" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils analyse how Macbeth is presented as a tragic hero. They first
  deepen their understanding of Shakespearean tragedy and tragic heroes, and then use this
  knowledge to analyse key scenes from the play. Finally, they prepare an essay on how
  Macbeth is presented as a tragic hero."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' understanding of Macbeth's plot, characters
  and themes from 'Macbeth: Lady Macbeth as a Machiavellian villain'. In this unit, they move
  away from a study of Lady Macbeth, and instead apply their knowledge and analytical skills to
  Macbeth's role in the tragedy. This is a culmination of all the knowledge developed on
  Shakespearean tragedy from their earlier readings of 'Macbeth' and 'Othello'. This unit also
  prepares pupils for their second deep dive into 'Macbeth', when they will focus on the role
  of masculinity and how it precipitates Macbeth's tragic downfall.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-168-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-168-2 ,
