    natcurric:scheme-english-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-exploring-the-gothic ,
    oakcurric:thread-nineteenth-century-literature .

oakcurric:unit-167
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Modern text: first deep dive"@en ;
  curric:slug "modern-text-first-deep-dive" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils learn about how Priestly questions societal expectations of
  gender and class in 'An Inspector Calls'. They look at three female characters, Sheila,
  Mrs Birling and Eva, and also explore how masculinity is presented. They finally plan and
  write an essay on the topic."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils learn about how Priestly questions societal
  expectations of gender and class in 'An Inspector Calls'. They look at three female
  characters, Sheila, Mrs Birling and Eva, and also explore how masculinity is presented. They
  finally plan and write an essay on the topic.""" ;
