oakcurric:unit-172
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Modern text: second deep dive"@en ;
  curric:slug "modern-text-second-deep-dive" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils explore how Priestly presents the Inspector and crime and
  punishment in 'An Inspector Calls'. They first look at different ways of interpreting the
  Inspector, before then thinking about what messages about crime and punishment Priestly is
  communicating."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit uses and builds on pupils' understanding of 'An Inspector Calls'
  from the first deep dive. It also extends and deepens their analytical thinking, so they are
  able to make more nuanced and tentative responses. Pupils now start to think more about the
  Inspector, and they start to link that to the play's wider themes and ideas, as well as
  Priestly's inentions. This prepares pupils for the final deep dive, where they will look more
  at how Priestly uses dramatic techniques to present those themes and ideas.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-172-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-172-2 ,
